The name Aachen is derived from the [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] name ''Aquae granni'', which meant "water of [[Grannus]]", a [[Celts|Celtic]] deity worshiped in the area.<ref name="tourism">Mielke, Rita (2013)</ref> As a [[spa]] city, Aachen could use the title ''Bad Aachen'', but as the town then would not appear in first place on alphabetically ordered lists, it declined to do so.{{citation needed|date=October 2013}} The city is known by a variety of different names in other languages:
